text.tspan: Ratio of wild-to-captive species in global wildlife trade
This measures the ratio of wild organisms to captive organisms that are traded globally. A higher ratio means it's
mostly wild species that are traded; a lower ratio means more captive species are traded.
Source: Harfoot et al. (2018). Unveiling the patterns and trends in 40 years of global trade in CITES-listed wildlife.
